## 3. Institutional vs. Individual (Competitive Landscape)

### How the Giants Do It
Fortune 500 retailers (Walmart, Target, Kroger) don't use spreadsheets. They use **Enterprise Revenue Management** and **Price Optimization** suites:
* **Key Players:** *SAP Revenue Management*, *PROS*, *Zilliant*, or *Revionics*.
* **The "High-End" Features:** These tools use AI to scrape competitor websites in real-time, factor in weather patterns, and even predict "cross-elasticity" (how raising the price of milk affects the sale of cereal).

### The MVP Strategy
Your vibe-coded MVP will skip the "AI-predictive modeling" and "competitor scraping." Instead, it focuses on the **Baseline Truth**. 
* **The Foundation:** By proving that the retailer is currently 4% behind the CPI, you provide the **"Moral Authority"** for the pricing team to take action. You are building the "Check Engine" light; the enterprise tools are the "Self-Driving System."

